Steve Chamberlin wrote:
> I'm looking for a good source of basic Lego Technic parts (beams, gears,
> axles, etc.) for robot construction.
<snip> 
> If anyone knows of a good source for these parts, or the Lego kit number of
> a good starter set, please let me know.

The best, cheapest place to get Lego Technic accessory parts is Lego
Shop-At-Home, 1-800-453-4652.  Ask 'em to send you a free catalog.  In
the back of each issue are a couple of pages showing all the
miscellaneous motors, pulleys, gears, etc.

